FBIS4-47809 "drafr086_a_94008" FBIS-AFR-94-086 Daily Report 4 May 1994 CENTRAL AFRICA Rwanda Three UN Soldiers Killed Three UN Soldiers Killed LD0405092894 Paris France-2 Television Network in French 0842 GMT 4 May 94 LD0405092894 Paris France-2 Television Network French BFN [Text] Three soldiers with the UN Mission in Rwanda [UNAMIR] were wounded on Tuesday [3 May] night during shelling of Kigali airport. A UNAMIR spokesman announced this as violent fighting was continuing in Kigali. Mortar shells which hit the airport were launched by the Rwandan Patriotic Front forces, who were responding to shots fired by the government forces.
